modules.description: This module facilitates the generation of RPC mechanisms by constructing and manipulating OCaml abstract syntax trees (ASTs), including expressions, patterns, and types, while handling parameter parsing, error propagation, and location tracking. It specializes in creating server-side functions, caches, and client wrappers that extend OCaml structures with RPC-specific logic, such as attribute-driven code generation and type-aware transformations. Commonly used for automating distributed system implementations in OCaml, it enables seamless integration of remote procedure calls with type-safe, location-aware AST manipulations.
